info.title: CISCO-ATM-QOS-MIB MIB API
info.description:
The MIB is created to provide ATM QoS information in
    these areas:
    
    1. Traffic shaping on a per-VC basis
    2. Traffic shaping on a per-VP basis 
    3. Per-VC queuing/buffering
    
    Although the initial requirements of the MIB are
    driven to support the GSR TAZ line card,
    CISCO-ATM-QOS-MIB is designed as a generic MIB to
    support ATM interfaces across all platforms.
    
    Here are the tables defined in this MIB:
    ciscoAtmQosVccTable 
         - to provide information on traffic shaping on 
           a per-VC basis.
                          
    ciscoAtmQosVpcTable 
         - to provide information on traffic shaping on
           a per-VP basis.
        
    ciscoAtmQosVcQueuingTable
    ciscoAtmQosVcQueuingClassTable
         - to provide information on per-VC
           queuing/buffering.

⚠️ **IMPORTANT - MIB DATA ACCESS**:
This YANG model exists for SMIv2-to-YANG translation purposes, but MIB data on IOS-XE devices is primarily accessed via **SNMP protocol**, not RESTCONF.

**RESTCONF Limitation**: Many MIB paths may return 404 errors via RESTCONF `/data` endpoints because the device exposes MIB data through SNMP, not the YANG datastore.

**Recommended Access Methods**:
- Use SNMP (v2c/v3) to query MIB data directly
- Use NETCONF `<get>` operations for devices supporting YANG-modeled MIB access
- Check device capabilities: some newer IOS-XE versions may support limited RESTCONF access to specific MIBs

**YANG Model Purpose**: These YANG models define the structure of SNMP MIBs in YANG format for tooling compatibility, but do not guarantee RESTCONF data availability.

CISCO-ATM-QOS-MIB_CISCO-ATM-QOS-MIB.description:
This table is defined to provide QoS information for
        each active ATM VC existing on the interface.

caqVccParamsType.description: The service category of this virtual circuit connection.

caqVccParamsPcrIn0.description:
Input Peak Cell Rate (PCR) in kbps with 
            Cell Loss Priority bit set to 0 (clp0).

caqVccParamsPcrIn01.description:
Number of OAM F5 end to end loopback cells sent through
            the VCC.

caqVccParamsPcrOut0.description:
Output Peak Cell Rate (PCR) in kbps with
            Cell Loss Priority bit set to 0 (clp0).

caqVccParamsPcrOut01.description:
Output Peak Cell Rate (PCR) in kbps with
            Cell Loss Priority bit set to 1 (clp01).

caqVccParamsScrIn0.description:
Input Sustained Cell Rate (SCR) in kbps
            for connection with VBR type of QoS and
            Cell Loss Priority bit set to 0 (clp0).

caqVccParamsScrIn01.description:
Input Sustained Cell Rate (SCR) in kbps
            for connection with VBR type of QoS and
            Cell Loss Priority bit set to 1 (clp01).

caqVccParamsScrOut0.description:
Output Sustained Cell Rate (SCR) in kbps
            for connection with VBR type of QoS and
            Cell Loss Priority bit set to 0 (clp0).

caqVccParamsScrOut01.description:
Output Sustained Cell Rate (SCR) in kbps
            for connection with VBR type of QoS and
            Cell Loss Priority bit set to 1 (clp01).

caqVccParamsBcsIn0.description:
Input Burst Cell Size (BCS) for connection
            with VBR type of QoS and
            Cell Loss Priority bit set to 0 (clp0).

caqVccParamsBcsIn01.description:
Input Burst Cell Size (BCS) for connection
            with VBR type of QoS and
            Cell Loss Priority bit set to 1 (clp01).

caqVccParamsBcsOut0.description:
Output Burst Cell Size (BCS) for connection
            with VBR type of QoS and 
            Cell Loss Priority bit set to 0 (clp0).

caqVccParamsBcsOut01.description:
Output Burst Cell Size (BCS) for connection
            with VBR type of QoS and
            Cell Loss Priority bit set to 1 (clp01).

caqVccParamsInheritLevel.description: The source of configuration for peak cell rate.

caqVccParamsMcrIn.description:
Input Minimum Cell Rate (MCR) in kbps for
            connection with VBR-nrt or ABR type of QoS.

caqVccParamsMcrOut.description:
Output Minimum Cell Rate (MCR) in kbps for
            connection with VBR-nrt or ABR type of QoS.

caqVccParamsRfl.description: The source of configuration for rate factor.

caqVccParamsNrm.description: Maximum number of tx cells for each forward rm cell.

caqVccParamsInvTrm.description: Maximum time between forward rm cells.

caqVccParamsAdtf.description: Allowed cell rate decrease time factor.

caqVpcParamsVpState.description: VP state of the current permanent virtual path.

caqVpcParamsPeakRate.description:
Maximum rate in kbps at which the associated
            permanent virtual path can transmit data.

caqVpcParamsCesRate.description:
Maximum rate in kbps at which CES VCs can transmit
            data with the associated permanent virtual path.

caqVpcParamsDataVcCount.description:
Number of data VCs currently associated with
            the permanent virtual path.

caqVpcParamsCesVcCount.description:
Number of CES VCs currently associated with
            the permanent virtual path.

caqVpcParamsVcdF4Seg.description: Vcd for F4 OAM segment processing.

caqVpcParamsVcdF4Ete.description: Vcd for F4 OAM end to end processing.

caqVpcParamsScr.description: Sustained cell rate associated with the PVP.

caqVpcParamsMbs.description: Maximum burst size associated with the PVP.

caqVpcParamsAvailBw.description:
Bandwidth in Kbps currently currently available
            on this PVP.

caqQueuingParamsMeanQDepth.description:
Mean Queue Depth associated with the vc.  This value
            is calculated based on the actual queue depth on the
            interface and the exponential weighting constant.

caqQueuingParamsClassIndex.description:
A class index, which associates with an IP precedence
            (0 to 8), is defined to reference individual
            caqQueuingParamsClassEntry.

caqQueuingParamsClassRandDrp.description:
Number of packets dropped when Mean Queue
            Length is between Minimum Threshold and
            Maximum Threshold range.

caqQueuingParamsClassTailDrp.description:
Number of packets dropped because the Mean
            Queue Depth exceeds the Maximum Threshold value.

caqQueuingParamsClassMrkProb.description:
Mark probability denominator.  This is the value used
            in the calculation of a packet being dropped when
            the average queue size is between the minimum
            threshold and the maximum threshold.

caqQueuingParamsTable.description:
This table provides queuing related information
        for a VC existing on an ATM interface.

caqQueuingParamsMeanQDepth.description:
Mean Queue Depth associated with the vc.  This value
            is calculated based on the actual queue depth on the
            interface and the exponential weighting constant.

caqQueuingParamsClassTable.description:
This table provides queuing information for all 
        queuing classes associating with a VC.

caqQueuingParamsClassIndex.description:
A class index, which associates with an IP precedence
            (0 to 8), is defined to reference individual
            caqQueuingParamsClassEntry.

caqQueuingParamsClassRandDrp.description:
Number of packets dropped when Mean Queue
            Length is between Minimum Threshold and
            Maximum Threshold range.

caqQueuingParamsClassTailDrp.description:
Number of packets dropped because the Mean
            Queue Depth exceeds the Maximum Threshold value.

caqQueuingParamsClassMrkProb.description:
Mark probability denominator.  This is the value used
            in the calculation of a packet being dropped when
            the average queue size is between the minimum
            threshold and the maximum threshold.
